,{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cocoapods.JivoSDK\/documentation\/JivoSDK\/JVSessionController\/shutDown()","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It means, for example, if your client logs-out and then logs-in again, you may see him as entirely new client."},{"text":"\n","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Even in case he uses the same login credentials, and even in case you provide the same user_token for him into SDK."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To keep chat history alive between login sessions, you have to generate JWT token and use it as user_token."},{"text":"\n","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Below, we explain how to do that."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","text":"#1: Prepare secret","anchor":"1-Prepare-secret","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"First, you need to create your global ","type":"text"},{"code":"secret","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" which you’ll use for generating JWT tokens."},{"type":"text","text":"\n"},{"type":"text","text":"Please create it accordingly to RFC 7519, with length of 256 bit."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Then, place this secret into “JWT Settings” screen of your Mobile SDK channel options.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"aside","name":"Tip","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You may found this resource useful to generate, sign, and check JWT tokens: ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/jwt.io\/","isActive":true}]}],"style":"tip"},{"anchor":"2-Generate-token","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"#2: Generate token"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"JWT tokens you will generate for your clients, must:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"contain unique “id” field for each individual client"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragrap